==English==
===Variant spelling===
[[avellan]]
===Etymology===
Italian ''[[avellana]]'' a filbert, from Latin ''[[Avella]]'' or ''[[Abella]]'' a city of Campania.
===Adjective===
'''avellane'''
#''(Heraldry):'' In the form of four unhusked [[filbert]]s; as, an avellane cross.

